The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 UltraTech first-quarter net up

 OUR BUREAU

 Mumbai, July 25: UltraTech Ltd, the Aditya Birla group firm, has reported a robust growth in earnings for the first quarter ended June 30, 2006. Profit after tax rose close to 251 per cent at Rs 211 crore compared with Rs 60 crore in the same period last year.

 Net sales grew 49 per cent year-on-year at Rs 1,180 crore against Rs 793 crore last year. 

 Profit before interest stood at Rs 23 crore, up from Rs 22 crore last year. 

 The first quarter performance of the company has seen an improved growth in sales and net profit, driven by higher domestic realisation and volumes, the company said in a statement. 

 The company also reported a 104 per cent capacity utilisation across its units during the quarter compared with 95 per cent in the year-ago period.

 The domestic sales volume grew by 10 per cent ahead of the industry growth. Overall sales volume increased by 12 per cent. Cement exports stood at 3.48 lmt compared with 4.15 lmt in the first quarter of fiscal 2006.

 To address the issue of rising energy costs, UltraTech has earmarked a capital expenditure of around Rs 1,424 crore to be spent over the next three years. Of this, Rs 844 crore will be towards installation of captive power plants at the companys units in Gujarat and Chhattisgarh. 

 Indiabulls net rises

 Indiabulls Financial Services Ltd today announced an 87.2 per cent year-on-year rise in net profit at Rs 76.6 crore for the first quarter ended June 30, 2006 against Rs 40.9 crore a year ago.

 Total revenue increased 123 per cent at Rs 220.5 crore against Rs 98.6 crore in the same quarter last year. The consumer finance business comprising personal loans, used two-wheeler loans and loans against property grew at Rs 238.5 crore.

 The companys employee strength stood at 15,000 as on June 30, it said in a statement. 

 In its consumer finance business, outstanding loans grew 705 per cent year-on-year to Rs 238.59 crore from Rs 29.63 crore last year. 

 The same grew 111.2 per cent quarter-on-quarter from Rs 112.99 crore at the end of March, 2006.

 Welspun profit dips

 Welspun India Ltd has registered a 30 per cent drop in net profits at Rs 7.5 crore for the first quarter ended June 30, against Rs 10.8 crore in the corresponding period last year.

 The company has shown a 45.2 per cent rise in sales at Rs 199 crore against Rs 137 crore in the corresponding period last fiscal. 




